# Claude Code Insights

376 sessions total · 8 analyzed · 184 messages · 12h · 1 commits
2026-02-20 to 2026-02-22

## At a Glance

**What's working:** You're pushing Claude into genuinely ambitious territory — running autonomous agent personas (Deacon, Mayor) through extended patrol loops and using Claude as real system orchestration, not just a code assistant. You're also disciplined about infrastructure: migrating your config into a tracked bare git repo and systematically replacing hard-coded paths shows you treat your AI tooling setup as proper infrastructure worth maintaining. See _Impressive Things You Did_.

**What's hindering you:** On Claude's side, it repeatedly jumps into action without verifying the actual state of your system first — making wrong assumptions about SSH security, breaking hard links with Write instead of in-place edits, and botching symlink directions. On your side, recurring SQLite bugs and vapor-phase wisp issues keep resurfacing across agent sessions because there's no persistent documentation of known issues, so each patrol session rediscovers the same problems from scratch. See _Where Things Go Wrong_.

**Quick wins to try:** Set up a CLAUDE.md file that documents your agent system's known bugs (the empty-ID SQLite rows, vapor-phase wisp limitations) and includes a rule like "always read and verify current state before modifying files" — this alone would cut down the biggest friction patterns you're hitting. Also try custom slash commands via Skills for your patrol startup sequence, so you don't have to re-explain the Deacon/Mayor workflow each session. See _Features to Try_.

**Ambitious workflows:** As models get more capable, your multi-agent patrol system is perfectly positioned for parallel sub-agents — one handling patrol cycles, another monitoring database integrity, and a third managing token refresh, so a single SQLite corruption or OAuth expiry doesn't block everything. Start documenting your agent protocols and known failure modes now so that when spawning resilient, self-healing agent networks becomes practical, you'll have the foundation ready to go. See _On the Horizon_.

